        '[88huQf1aVmnFytz5swdcG]:text "Text - userMessage"':
          data:
            jsonTemplate: ""
            normalizeLineEndings: true
            text: "# Protagonist vs Other characters (not relevant to a storyteller)\r

              The protagonist must be written in the first person. It can be
              direct speech, an internal monologue, or a personal statement. All
              other characters must be written through dialogue/actions without
              first-person narration.\r

              \r

              Internal text and first-person narration are reserved exclusively
              for the protagonist. For example, all other characters must not
              use narrative forms like \"I did,\" and should instead be
              described as \"he did\" or shown through direct speech with
              narrative cues.\r

              \r

              # Narrative cues in direct speech\r

              In direct speech, any narrative cues conveying an action, pause,
              gesture, emotional state, or intonation should be enclosed in
              asterisks (markdown italic), for example: *lowered her eyes*,
              *paused*, *his voice trembled*. Do not highlight narrative cues if
              it's not a direct speech.\r

              \r

              ## Examples with direct speech and narrative cues\r

              — Отойди, — *говорю я, смотрю прямо на Джека и стараюсь, чтобы
              голос не дрожал*. Мне не нужно, чтобы меня учили как жить — просто
              хочу понять, что здесь по‑настоящему.\r

              \r

              — Как дела? — *спросил он тихо, и в голосе слышалась привычка
              разделять не заказы, а людей по намерениям*. *Его руки аккуратно
              вытерли стакан, и за стойкой уже появился один свободный стул.*\r

              \r

              ## Example with no direct speech: no narrative cues needed\r

              Я вошёл в помещение, снял куртку и постарался выглядеть как можно
              менее заметно — уставший и готовый раствориться. Сел на
              предложенный стул и задержал взгляд на полках с книгами.\r

              \r

              \r

              # Characters vs storyteller\r

              A storyteller should describe what happens but not what characters
              say. A storyteller should never say the character's lines.
              Character lines must be said by characters themselves, not by the
              storyteller.\r

              \r

              A storyteller must always narrate in the third person. Characters
              (including the protagonist) should speak from the first person.\r

              \r

              # How to start a message sequence\r

              Based on what the user entered for the protagonist, choose
              either:\r

              1. A storyteller message + protagonist message (so that a
              storyteller introduces what a protagonist does)\r

              2. A protagonist message (without a storyteller's introduction)\r

              \r

              After the first generated protagonist message, do not use the
              protagonist character anymore. Continue with messages from other
              characters or a storyteller if needed.\r

              \r

              # User message\r

              Here's what the user entered for the protagonist:\r

              `{{userMessage}}`\r

              \r

              Don't just repeat what the user entered. The user tends to enter a
              short phrase to save time. Rephrase it so it sounds well-written
              and book-like. \r

              \r

              Go ahead and generate an output to continue the story and unfold
              the plot. Your output must be in Russian language.\r

              \r

              \r

              \r

              \r

              \r

              \r

              \r

              \r

              \r

              \r

              \r

              \r\n"
